    <div class="book3">
        <div class="book-title"><b>Name:</b>Tacos al Pastor</div>
        <div class="book-auth"><b>Cuisine:</b>Mexican</div>
        <div class="book-pub"><b>Popularity:</b>★★★★☆</div>
        <div class="book-pri"><b>Price:</b>$1 - $3 per taco</div>
        <div class="book-exp"><b>Overview:</b>Tacos al Pastor are a popular street food in Mexico, influenced by Lebanese immigrants who introduced the concept of shawarma. The dish consists of marinated pork, cooked on a vertical spit (similar to shawarma), and served on small corn tortillas. It is typically garnished with pineapple, onions, cilantro, and a variety of salsas.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="book4">
        <div class="book-title"><b>Name:</b>Peking Duck</div>
        <div class="book-auth"><b>Cuisine:</b> Chinese</div>
        <div class="book-pub"><b>Popularity:</b>★★★★☆</div>
        <div class="book-pri"><b>Price:</b>$40 - $80 per dish</div>
        <div class="book-exp"><b>Overview:</b> Peking Duck is a famous Chinese dish known for its crispy skin and tender meat. The duck is seasoned, air-dried, and roasted until the skin is crispy and golden brown. It is traditionally served with thin pancakes, hoisin sauce, and sliced green onions. Diners assemble their own pancakes with slices of duck, skin, and condiments.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="book5">
        <div class="book-title"><b>Name:</b> Croissant</div>
