        <div class="book-exp"><b>Overview:</b>The croissant is a buttery, flaky, and crescent-shaped pastry that originated in France. Made from a laminated dough, which involves folding butter into the dough multiple times to create thin layers, the croissant is a staple of French bakeries and cafes. It can be enjoyed plain or filled with ingredients like chocolate or almond paste.</div>
